metadata.abstract: The text discusses a comparative analysis of the ordinary repertory from Aquileia and Cividale, highlighting the influence of German and Central European melodies, as well as regional variations in the liturgical sources. It emphasizes the intercultural position of Aquileia, noting the significant German influence due to historical factors, and suggests that further research should focus on identifying this influence rather than defining an independent Aquileian liturgy. The study also points out the methodological challenges and limitations in analyzing the sources and calls for a cautious interpretation of the findings.
